



Gentn
Mount Vernon 26th Augt 1759



I shall draw upon you in a few days to the Amount of about 150 in two Setts of Exchange: the one payable to Messrs Champe and Hunter of Virginia and the other to Mr Richd Washington of London.1 I did not think it amiss to give you this earliest advice (via Whitehaven) of my Intentions but should not have doubted your Acceptance of my Bills without it as I in a former of the 12th June advertisd you of my Marriage with Mrs Martha Custis Relict of Danl P. Custis Esqr. deceasdby which I am empowerd to draw for the Estates money in your hands. I am Gentn Yr Most Obedt Servt

Go: Washington

